<H3> <TI>   Tanks Get Advanced Fire, Explosion Suppression System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tanks Get Advanced Fire, Explosion Suppression System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1605102994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1605102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Defense Institute for Fire Research in New 
Delhi has developed a fire fighting system that can detect and 
put out fires in less than one-fourth of a second. The director 
of the institute, Major General B.S. Kataria, said the automatic 
fire and explosion suppression system, as it is called, has been 
fitted on the MBT [Main Battle Tank]-Arjun tank and is to be 
fitted also on the T-72 tanks. He said this fire fighting 
system has been integrated with another system to alert the tank 
crew in the event of a nuclear, biological, and chemical attack. 
The fire protection system can also be fitted in ships and 
armored personnel carriers. 

</TEXT>

