<H4>    DPRK Agrees to IAEA Visit on Fuel Rods Removal </H4>

<F P=102> AU2105133094 Paris AFP in English 1309 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2105133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, May 21 (AFP) -- North Korea has agreed to 
the visit of a new high-level mission of the International 
Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) to discuss the removal of fuel rods 
from its Yongbyon nuclear complex, the IAEA announced Saturday. 
  The mission will leave Vienna Sunday [22 May] and arrive in 
North Korea Tuesday. 
  "It will clarify inspection measures necessary in relation 
with the discharging of the reactor, an IAEA statement said. 

</TEXT>

