<H4>    Laboratory Inspection Completed </H4>

<F P=102> AU2505120094 Paris AFP in English 1141 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2505120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, May 25 (AFP) -- Inspectors from the 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) have completed their 
inspection of a controversial experimental laboratory in North 
Korea and took samples from spent fuel rods, IAEA officials said 
in Vienna Wednesday. 
  The samples should allow the IAEA to determine how long the 
fuel rods were in the reactor and thereby calculate whether 
plutonium could have been diverted, possibly for use in making 
nuclear bombs. 

</TEXT>

