<H3> <TI>   Country May Conduct Second Test of Missile `Soon' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Country May Conduct Second Test of Missile `Soon' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2805004994 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0000 GMT 28 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2805004994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Yi Il-hwa from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] Quoting a Japanese military source, YOMIURI SHIMBUN 
reported today that North Korea is making moves to test-fire a 
missile. 
  According to this military source, a U.S. information 
satellite caught these moves by North Korea, and the U.S. 
Government informed the Japanese Government of this. 
  The military source said it is highly possible that North 
Korea will soon carry out the second missile test fire which 
follows its first test fire of the Nodong No. 1 missile toward 
the East Sea in May of last year. 
  Regarding these moves by North Korea at a time when it is 
the 
focus of the international community because of its nuclear 
issue, the Japanese military source analyzed that North Korea is 
trying to test-fire a missile while weather over the East Sea is 
calm. 

</TEXT>

