<H3> <TI>   IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hizballah Official on Reprisals </H4>

<F P=102> NC2305144294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1310 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2305144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Beirut, 23 May (MENA)--A political official in 
Hizballah has warned that the Lebanese Islamic resistance will 
respond violently to the abduction of Shaykh Mustafa al-Dirani 
by Israeli commandos two days ago. The official predicted a 
rise in effective attacks by the Islamic resistance in the near 
future. Israel may be able to abduct hostages, he said, but it 
cannot twist the arm of the resistance or dissuade it from 
pursuing its strategic task of confronting occupation and 
repelling aggression against the Lebanese people and land. 
[passage omitted] 
  Reiterating Hizballah's position on the Israeli navigator, 
al-Musawi said that Hizballah has no information about the 
navigator's fate. He pointed out that Mustafa al-Dirani, 
although a resistance figure, has no organizational link with 
Hizballah. 
  'Ammar al-Musawi expressed doubt that al-Dirani has any 
information about the Israeli navigator. He expressed his 
belief that Israel, in carrying out the abduction, may have 
benefited from some loopholes in the internal security 
situation. Al-Musawi said that the Lebanese authorities have an 
urgent duty to protect the resistance in every part of Lebanon, 
north or south. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-46131 </DOCNO>
