  [Text] There have been some 100 attacks and attempted 
attacks, in which four Israelis have been killed and 13 have 
been wounded, since the signing of the Gaza-Jericho agreement. 
There have been no attacks inside the Green Line, security 
sources told correspondents. 
  They said that immediately after the signing of the 
agreement 
there was a sharp increase in attempted attacks with live 
ammunition against IDF [Israel Defense Forces] installations set 
up in the Qatif Bloc and against IDF patrols. The sources 
stressed that some 200 wanted men, mostly Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] and Islamic Jihad members, remained at 
large in the territories. 

