  [Text] The Organization of the Islamic Revolution Army for 
the Liberation of Palestine [munazzamat jaysh al-thawrah 
al-islamiyah li tahrir filastin] has claimed responsibility for 
the operation it carried out against the Zionist occupation 
forces in the Rshaf area in the occupied zone of southern 
Lebanon on Saturday [14 May]. In a statement, the organization 
said its Gaza Fedayeen group penetrated the Zionist enemy's 
front in Rshaf, killing and wounding a number of Zionist 
soldiers. 
  Following this heroic operation, the Zionist enemy forces 
shelled the liberated areas adjacent to the occupied zone in 
southern Lebanon with mortar and artillery. 

