<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Demand Drugs, Money, Weapons </H4>

<F P=102> LD2605125294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1224 GMT 26 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2605125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Roman Zadunaiskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- Four unidentified terrorists 
seized some 30 hostages in a bus near the city of Mineralnye 
Vody in northern Caucasus on Thursday. 
  According to the Russian Ministry for Emergency Situations, 
they are armed with three submachine guns and a grenade. The 
terrorists demand drugs, a helicopter without a crew, 10 million 
U.S. dollars, four submachine guns, four flack jackets, a 
grenade launcher and a night sight. 
  The "Ikarus" coach was en route from Vladikavkaz in North 
Ossetia to Stavropol in southern Russia. 

</TEXT>

