<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Krasnodar Kray Militia on Alert </H4>

<F P=102> LD2605205894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1830 GMT 
26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Any unexpected actions or movements by the 
terrorists who seized the bus carrying passengers could also 
affect Stavropol Kray's neighbour, Krasnodar Kray, as was the 
case very recently during similar events in Rostov. The 
Krasnodar Kray militia has therefore been placed on full combat 
readiness, an ITAR-TASS correspondent learned from the kray 
interior affairs directorate. 
  A telephone conference was held with chiefs from town and 
rayon militia departments, which also is heightening the 
readiness of personnel in case there were unexpected 
developments in the operational situation. 
  Preparations were made for a helicopter carrying special 
purpose subunits to fly to Mineralnyye Vodiy, but its departure 
was postponed after special purpose troops from Moscow arrived 
there. 

</TEXT>

