<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Four Hostages Released for Money </H4>

<F P=102> LD2705042094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0303 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705042094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Styazhkin] </F>
  [Text] Mineralnyye Vody (Stavropol Kray), 27 May -- As a 
result of negotiations held during the night, $4 million were 
handed over to the terrorists who had seized the bus with over 
30 passengers near Mineralnyye Vody yesterday at about noon. 
Having received the money, the terrorists released four more 
hostages but they are still insisting that the sum of $10 
million be delivered to them. 
  The four terrorists spent last night in the bus with tightly 
closed doors on the territory of the Mineralnyye Vody airport. 
They are holding 14 people hostage. 
  It is thought that early in the morning the terrorists took 
turns taking naps while keepng a close eye on the hostages and 
making sure that no one could approach the bus. 

</TEXT>

