<F P=101> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   PKK Leader Ocalan Orders Regrouping After Heavy Losses </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PKK Leader Ocalan Orders Regrouping After Heavy Losses </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2505203494 London Kanal-6 Television in Turkish 1600 GMT 
25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2505203494 </F>
<F P=104>  London Kanal-6 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The route suffered by the PKK [Kurdish Workers 
Party] at the hands of the security forces in recent days has 
been admitted by the leader of the organization Abdullah Ocalan. 
Ocalan severely warned the members of the organization, saying 
that there has been an incredible number of losses. 
  [Correspondent Fatih Yilmaz] According to available 
information, in his message to PKK field commanders the previous 
day Ocalan said that those responsible for the losses will be 
punished. Ocalan demanded that those not fighting voluntarily be 
dismissed from the organization and called on the PKK to carry 
out low-risk operations such as laying mines, sabotage, and road 
blocks. 
  The PKK conducted mine-laying and roadblock operations 
yesterday. 
  In his message, PKK leader Ocalan said that the losses 
suffered by the organization in Pulumur and Dogubeyazit are 
unacceptably high, and made the following assessment: The field 
commanders are misleading me, the information they provide does 
not conform with reality. 
  The PKK suffered huge losses during operations carried out 
by 
the security forces in the last few months. 
  In the meantime, the mop-up operation launched by the 
security forces on Cudi Mountain is continuing. It is reported 
that major losses has been inflicted on the PKK. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

