<H3> <TI>   Two Istanbul Incidents Employ Concussion Grenades </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Istanbul Incidents Employ Concussion Grenades </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Timed Bomb in Train Station </H4>

<F P=102> TA2505053094 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0430 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2505053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two people have been slightly injured after four 
concussion grenades [ses bombasi], set with a timing mechanism, 
exploded in Istanbul's Harem Station. The concussion grenades, 
planted at the train station by unidentified people, went off at 
short intervals beginning at approximately 2300 last night. 
  Sevki Mustafaoglu was wounded in the leg and taken to 
Haydarpasa Hospital, and Murat Yaman was treated at the site. 
  Officials stated that one of the concussion grenades was 
placed inside a phone booth, another at a coffee shop, and 
another at the back entrance to a police station in the train 
station, adding that an investigation is under way. 
  Meanwhile, at around the same time, a Molotov cocktail was 
thrown at Sisli's Bag-Kur [Social Security Association for 
Tradesmen, Artisans, and Independent Workers] building. No one 
was injured in the incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

