<H3> <TI>   German Decision To Extradite `Terrorists' Welcomed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    German Decision To Extradite `Terrorists' Welcomed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2005075994 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2005075994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It has been announced that Turkey welcomes the 
German decision to extradite certain terrorists who violate the 
laws and engage in terrorist activities and that it is ready to 
receive those who will be extradited. 
  A Foreign Ministry statement on the issue notes that Turkey 
has, on various occasions in the past, announced that the death 
sentence has not been implemented in the country for the last 10 
years and that every legal and operative measure has been taken 
to prevent torture. Stressing that Turkish-German talks are 
continuing on the preparation of a memorandum of understanding 
concerning those to be extradited, the statement expresses the 
hope that a solution will be reached on the issue soon. The 
statement continues: We are sorry [words indistinct] efforts 
by certain German states to prevent the extradition of these 
persons. No one should doubt that Turkey, just like Germany, is 
a state of law and everyone should refrain from behavior that 
might encourage acts of terror. The existing friendship and 
mutual trust between Turkey and Germany is the strongest 
guarantee to the solution of such problems. 

</TEXT>

