    The following list includes terrorism-related video 
reports extracted from FBIS Video Program Summaries from 19 to 
27 May, ordered alphabetically by country. Each entry is 
prefaced by the name of the city where the report originated, 
followed by the FBIS TV Center order number (e.g., BOG 94-001) 
and the date of broadcast. Tapes may be ordered by calling 
1-800-822-5115 for subscribers in Virginia and 1-800-542-8660 
for those outside Virginia. Tapes are available for 30 days and 
are for U.S. Government official use only. 
<H5>  Algeria/Russia </H5>
  Moscow MOS 94-5350 (20 May)--Correspondent's report from 
Algiers on terrorism in Algeria, recent killing of three 
Russians. 
<H5>  Brazil/Germany </H5>
  Rio Globo TV 231600 (23 May)--Report on Lufthansa Boeing 
plane making emergency landing at Brasilia airport after 
receiving bomb threat. 
<H5>  Iraq </H5>
  London LIT 94-066 (19 May)--English-language broadcast. 
"3-D" program covers Iraq's nuclear program. Footage includes 
shots of nuclear facilities (15 min). 
<H5>  Israel/Lebanon </H5>
  Madrid MAD 94-135 and Paris PAR 94-280, 94-281 (21 
May)--Report on Israel kidnapping Lebanese fundamentalist 
al-Dirani. 
  Tehran TEH 94-148 (26 May)--Iranian correspondent's report 
from site of al-Dirani kidnapping, shots of al-Dirani's family. 
<H5>  Russia </H5>
  Yekaterinberg YEK 94-101 (18 Apr)--Report on carbomb 
discovered during repairs at a service station. Footage shows 
service station, explosive device. Rest of report tells 
businessmen how to react if they find explosives. (1.5 min). A 
second item reports the investigation into hired assassinations 
in Verkh-Isetskiy District. Footage shows confiscated weapons, 
other materials; interview with local security chief (4 min). 
  Nizhniy Novgorod NIZ 94-077 (21 Apr)--"Aurochs" program 
interviews businessman N.I. Navilov, general director of 
Sverdlov explosives factory in Dzerzhinsk. Footage shows 
factory, equipment, products; Navilov interviewed on uses of 
explosives (18 min) 
  Madrid MAD 29-139, Moscow MOS 94-5371, and Paris PAR 
94-290 (26 May)--Report on children held hostage. 
  Ankara ANK 94-114 (27 May)--Footage of hijacked bus and 
security forces (1 min). 
  Berlin BER 94-172 (27 May)--Hostage incident concludes. 
<H5>  South Africa </H5>
  Johannesburg JOH 94-144 (20 May)--32 right-wingers accused 
of terrorism granted bail. 
<H5>  Spain </H5>
  Moscow MRT 94-261 (23 May)--Report on bomb in Madrid. 
  Madrid MAD 29-139 (26 May)--Report on controversy over 
authenticity of ETA extortion letter. 
<H5>  Turkey </H5>
  Ankara ANK 94-113 (26 May)--Footage of "terrorists" 
arrested in Izmir (2 min). 

