<DATE1>   21 May 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prince Charles Escaped Assassination in St. Petersburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prince Charles Escaped Assassination in St. Petersburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105223694 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 2155 GMT 21 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It looks as though someone planned an attempt on the 
life of Prince Charles, the Prince of Wales, when he visited St. 
Petersburg between 16 and 19 May. On 16 May, security guards 
discovered a plastic bag containing a time bomb between the 
doors of a shop of the British firm Littlewoods in Tukhachevskiy 
Avenue. The alarm hand connected with the firing device and 
four kilograms of TNT pointed at eight o'clock. Had the 
explosive device gone off, the shop would have been blown to 
pieces. The Prince of Wales did visit Littlewoods, but at 
another time. 

</TEXT>

