<H3> <TI>   State of Emergency Extended in Cusco </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State of Emergency Extended in Cusco </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1905202594 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1905202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has extended the state of emergency 
until 19 July in the Paruro, Acomayo, Chumbivilcas, Canas and 
Canchis Provinces, Cusco Department. Houses may be searched 
without a warrant and restrictions are imposed on peoples' right 
to move freely from one place to another and to assemble 
peacefully. Arrests cannot be made without a warrant issued by a 
court or by the police unless a criminal is caught red-handed. 
  The supreme decree, published in EL PERUANO, states that the 
state of exception seeks to expedite antiterrorist operations in 
that region. 

</TEXT>

