<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Guatemalan Guerrilla Activities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Guatemalan Guerrilla Activities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2605132794 </F>
<F P=103> PA2605132794 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Guatemalan guerrilla activities monitored through 25 
May. 
  Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity, URNG, guerrillas on 
16 May attacked a farm in Malacatan, San Marcos, and stole 
14,000 quetzales. Farmers in that area have recently reported 
that guerrillas are demanding "war taxes" from them. (Guatemala 
City LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 17 May 94 p 8) 
  A presumed guerrilla was arrested on 22 May when the police 
and Army raided a house in Pujujil, Solola, discovering an arms 
cache containing weapons, uniforms, and medicines. (Guatemala 
City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 23 May 94 p 127) 

</TEXT>

