<H3> <TI>   JRA Says Washington, Tokyo Exaggerate DPRK Threat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    JRA Says Washington, Tokyo Exaggerate DPRK Threat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0106032694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0243 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0106032694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 1 KYODO -- The Japanese Government is 
exaggerating the threat from North Korea over its refusal to 
allow international inspections of its nuclear facilities, the 
Japanese Red Army claims in statements reaching Japan on 
Wednesday [1 Jun]. 
  The statements, sent to the Red Army's contacts in Japan, 
mark the May 30, 1972, Red Army machine-gun and grenade attack 
on passengers at Lod Airport in Tel Aviv, Israel. 
  That attack was carried out as a mark of solidarity with the 
Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine. 
  This year's statement claims the United States is creating 
tensions by using the threat from North Korea to promote its own 
plans to achieve nuclear exclusivity. 
  "The Japanese Government also accepts this and, in line with 
the United Nations, is agitating over whether or not to 
introduce sanctions," the statement says. 
  The statement also says Japan should reflect on its 
aggression during World War II and observe the spirit of peace 
enunciated in Article 9 of its constitution. 
  It says the Red Army opposes Japan's bid for a permanent 
seat 
on the UN Security Council. 

</TEXT>

