<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   13 June 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> COLOMBIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Colombian Guerrilla Activities Through 1 June </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Colombian Guerrilla Activities Through 1 June </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0206040994 </F>
<F P=103> PA0206040994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Colombian guerrilla activities monitored through 1 
June. 
  A few hours after the Cano Limon-Covenas Pipeline had 
resumed 
operations following 20 days of semiparalysis by the fire that 
destroyed five plants, guerrillas dynamited the line yesterday, 
knocking it out of service. The rebel attack, which caused the 
spilling of more than 5,000 barrels of crude, occurred at km 437 
in the Municipality of El Tarra, in northern Santander 
Department. (Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 28 May 94 
p9a) 
  The murder of Aguedo Calle, a member of the Communist 
Party's 
regional electoral commission, Chigorodo, in the Uraba banana 
region, disclosed on Thursday evening the existence of a new 
group that takes justice into its own hands. Although the new, 
self- styled, paramilitary group the "People's Children" (Hijos 
del Pueblo) has not claimed responsibility for the crime, 
authorities believe it was one of its actions. Alleged 
spokespersons for that group have sent a communique to the 
Chigorodo Municipal Prosecuting Office claiming responsibility 
for the murder of Gabriel Ortega, the Patriotic Union candidate 
for mayor, who was shot in Chigorodo last week. (Santa Fe de 
Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 28 May 94 p 9a) 
  A guerrilla terrorist plan to destroy political and 
government offices, as well as the Justice Palace in Cucuta, was 
discovered in northern Santander Department yesterday. In 
addition, an action to disrupt the elections in Cali was 
discovered by the 3d Army Brigade. Meanwhile, the killing of two 
soldiers and wounding of six were the results of a clash between 
troops of the 12th Army Brigade and FARC (Revolutionary Armed 
Forces of Colombia) rebels in Guacamayas, San Vicente del Caguan 
(Caqueta). (Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 29 May 94 p 
24A) 
  Three members of the Civil Registry Office in Cucuta who 
were 
kidnapped last Sunday by Army of National Liberation rebels were 
released last night. The three officials are safe and sound. 
(Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 
31 May 94) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

