<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Colombian Guerrilla Activities Through 30 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Colombian Guerrilla Activities Through 30 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3105150194 </F>
<F P=103> PA3105150194 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Colombian guerrilla activities monitored through 30 
May. 
  Medellin police authorities have issued a communique 
explaining the bomb attack on 22 May at Atanasio Girardot 
Stadium in Medellin was not directed against the members of the 
German soccer team which played that day. General Luis Ernesto 
Gilibert Vargas, Medellin police commander, has said the 
terrorist attack was exclusively directed against the members of 
a police patrol who were going home after concluding their 
patrol duties at the stadium. Two policemen were killed, and 
two were wounded in the attack. (Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO 
in Spanish 25 May 94 p 8B) 
  Six guerrillas and an Army officer were killed and two 
guerrillas and two soldiers were wounded during guerrilla 
actions in Boyaca and Antioquia Departments. In addition, 
guerrillas of the Simon Bolivar Guerrilla Coordinating Board 
have burned a bus in Santa Fe de Bogota. An Army lieutenant was 
killed in Boyaca Department in a clash with guerrillas of the 
38th Front of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia. 
(Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 27 May 94 p 6A) 

</TEXT>

